  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "However, since there is less focus on cross-prompt AES research, we have chosen to discuss them under this category.",
    "Cozma et al. (2018) proposed a method that combines a string kernel and word embedding representation with a Support Vector Machine (SVM) for prompt-specific and cross-prompt AES tasks.",
    "The essay script is represented using two approaches: the Histogram Intersection String Kernel (HISK) and the Bag-of-Super-Word-embeddings (BOSWE).",
    "The HISK representation captures similarity by considering common n-gram characters, while the BOSWE representation captures semantic similarity by utilizing word2vec embeddings.",
    "By combining these two representations and applying an SVM model, a score is predicted for the essay."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Cozma et al. (2018) proposed a method that combines a string kernel and word embedding representation with a Support Vector Machine (SVM) for prompt-specific and cross-prompt AES tasks."
  ]
}